llows from the Poisson summation formula and periodic gauge. Using the Fourier transformed\n\npotential V\u2113\u2113\u2032(r) =1\n\nqNP\n\nq\u2208EBZe\u2212iq\u00b7rV\u2113\u2113\u2032(q), the interaction then takes the form\n\n\u02c6V=X\n\n\u2113\u2113\u2032X\n\nq\u2208EBZV\u2113\u2113\u2032(q) : \u02c6\u03c1q\u2113\u02c6\u03c1\u2212q\u2113\u2032: (C7)\n\nwhere colons denote normal ordering with respect to the vacuum.", "embedding": [-0.00019435484, -0.02148709, 0.041616272, -0.007546068, 0.0066764224, -0.002518909, -0.003144355, -0.0364038, -0.065507434, 0.07007846, 0.042348787, -0.0040989774, 0.034470797, -0.054253973, -0.0076200496, 0.02420641, -0.0065609636, -0.02006195, -0.062313233, 0.0015396671, 0.024599722, -0.007261138, -0.056593582, -0.03414361, -0.025270358, 0.028129773, 0.008868448, 0.010077431, 0.06230313, 0.04081302, 0.048271976, -0.05370535, 0.009580793, -0.056564927, -0.020935582, -0.0020052507, -0.019026646, -0.011314204, 0.02850714, -0.0146946795, 0.059873715, -0.007910383, -0.016300416, -0.009258353, -0.011443415, -0.013607792, -0.03083791, -0.009792726, -0.036409833, -0.079684, 0.014578486, 0.007783705, 0.04138105, -0.010572393, -0.031803183, 0.012651495, -0.019579249, -0.0152231725, -0.0013568945, -0.0043429583, 0.015143966, -0.023085192, -0.007894032, -0.046399, 0.0038142852, 0.03696989, -0.01712017, 0.09372197, -0.005088676, -0.028166585, 0.0040016584, -0.01859504, -0.045575432, 0.015732696, -0.03904288, 0.0052126613, -0.019982928, -0.034481358, -0.07020993, -0.004500005, -0.021843553, -0.029692879, -0.0059883124, 0.012634913, -0.012399092, -0.026586862, -0.019704234, -0.029398657, -0.000601608, 0.023521524, 0.03579822, 0.068901606, -0.006135844, -0.03203706, 0.008566858, 0.04674428, 0.0058926167, 0.024722079, 0.012264219, 0.00071851286, 0.033220705, 0.053647444, -0.032800935, 0.04307125, -0.031590637, 0.057210814, -0.0075263195, 0.0017988097, 0.020731326, -0.04036051, 0.018293703, -0.011814667, 0.010106928, 0.019072086, 0.00776532, 0.014512